originalText.text:
I scheduled with him via Zoc Doc. He sent a text to me 10:36pm the night before the appointment asking questions in order to see if we were a good fit and to confirm. I answered right away and asked about after insurance fees that he mentioned. I didn't get a response, so I called the number the next day as well as the number for him listed on Zoc Doc and both went to voicemail.

I went to the appointment and he was a no show even though I asked the receptionist to call him. I then got a text after the appointment apologizing and telling me that he doesn't accept my insurance (even though it's listed on Zoc Doc) and a link to information about out of network benefits.

Based on these interactions, the office that I visited, the lack of response I believe that he does this with everyone simply to lure unsuspecting people and tricking them into agreeing to pay for "holistic" therapy that is not covered by insurance most likely because he is not a real doctor and is trying to get around being on record.
